BT 0 g /F2 14 Tf 84.96000000000001 610 Td (Understanding Toddler Brain Development) Tj ET
q 0 G 1 w 50 600 m 382 600 l S Q
BT 0 g /F2 11 Tf 50 575 Td (Why Their Brain Is Different From Ours:) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F1 10 Tf 50 543 Td (The prefrontal cortex - the part of the brain responsible for) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F1 10 Tf 50 527 Td (impulse control, emotional regulation, planning, and reasoning -) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F1 10 Tf 50 511 Td (is NOT fully developed until approximately age 25.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F1 10 Tf 50 479 Td (In toddlers \(ages 1-4\), this area is barely beginning to form.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F1 10 Tf 50 463 Td (This means your toddler literally CANNOT:) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F1 10 Tf 50 431 Td (  * Control impulses consistently) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F1 10 Tf 50 415 Td (  * Manage big emotions without help) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F1 10 Tf 50 399 Td (  * Think logically when upset) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F1 10 Tf 50 383 Td (  * Understand consequences in the moment) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F1 10 Tf 50 367 Td (  * See things from another person's perspective) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F2 11 Tf 50 335 Td (Why Tantrums Are Normal and Developmentally Appropriate:) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F1 10 Tf 50 303 Td (Tantrums are NOT a sign of bad parenting or a 'bad child.') Tj ET
BT 0 g /F1 10 Tf 50 287 Td (They are a sign that your child's emotional brain \(the amygdala\)) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F1 10 Tf 50 271 Td (is working perfectly - it's sending big feelings that the) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F1 10 Tf 50 255 Td (underdeveloped prefrontal cortex cannot yet regulate.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F1 10 Tf 50 223 Td (Think of it this way: Your toddler has an adult-sized gas pedal) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F1 10 Tf 50 207 Td (\(emotions\) but baby-sized brakes \(self-regulation\). They need) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F1 10 Tf 50 191 Td (YOU to be their external brakes until their own develop.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F2 11 Tf 50 159 Td (Key Takeaway:) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F1 10 Tf 50 143 Td (Your job is not to stop tantrums. Your job is to help your) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F1 10 Tf 50 127 Td (child feel safe while experiencing big emotions, and to model) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F1 10 Tf 50 111 Td (the regulation skills they will eventually internalize.) Tj ET

endstream
endobj
