BT 0 g /F2 14 Tf 128.64 610 Td (Tantrum Response Flowchart) Tj ET
q 0 G 1 w 50 600 m 382 600 l S Q
BT 0 g /F1 10 Tf 50 575 Td (Follow these steps when your toddler is having a tantrum:) Tj ET
q 0.92 g 50 545 332 32 re f Q
BT 0 g /F2 10 Tf 55 564 Td (STEP 1: Is My Child Safe?) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F1 9 Tf 55 550 Td (Check for physical danger. Move objects, move child if needed.) Tj ET
q 0.92 g 50 500 332 32 re f Q
BT 0 g /F2 10 Tf 55 519 Td (STEP 2: Am I Calm?) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F1 9 Tf 55 505 Td (Take 3 deep breaths. You cannot regulate a child if dysregulated.) Tj ET
q 0.92 g 50 455 332 32 re f Q
BT 0 g /F2 10 Tf 55 474 Td (STEP 3: Get Close & Low) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F1 9 Tf 55 460 Td (Kneel to their level. Open body language. Soft eyes.) Tj ET
q 0.92 g 50 410 332 32 re f Q
BT 0 g /F2 10 Tf 55 429 Td (STEP 4: Validate the Emotion) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F1 9 Tf 55 415 Td (Name what they feel: 'You're really frustrated right now.') Tj ET
q 0.92 g 50 365 332 32 re f Q
BT 0 g /F2 10 Tf 55 384 Td (STEP 5: Set the Boundary \(if needed\)) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F1 9 Tf 55 370 Td ('I won't let you hit. Hitting hurts. I'm keeping everyone safe.') Tj ET
q 0.92 g 50 320 332 32 re f Q
BT 0 g /F2 10 Tf 55 339 Td (STEP 6: Wait) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F1 9 Tf 55 325 Td (Do not rush. Do not lecture. Be present. Let the storm pass.) Tj ET
q 0.92 g 50 275 332 32 re f Q
BT 0 g /F2 10 Tf 55 294 Td (STEP 7: Co-Regulate) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F1 9 Tf 55 280 Td (Offer comfort: hug, rocking, humming. Match their breathing.) Tj ET
q 0.92 g 50 230 332 32 re f Q
BT 0 g /F2 10 Tf 55 249 Td (STEP 8: Reconnect After) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F1 9 Tf 55 235 Td (Once calm: 'That was hard. I'm here. Let's figure this out.') Tj ET
BT 0 g /F2 10 Tf 50 180 Td (Key Principles:) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F1 9 Tf 50 164 Td (* Connection before correction) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F1 9 Tf 50 150 Td (* All feelings are allowed; not all behaviors are allowed) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F1 9 Tf 50 136 Td (* You are the calm in their storm) Tj ET

endstream
endobj
