BT 0 g /F2 13 Tf 97.44 610 Td (Emotion Coaching Scripts \(Page 1 of 5\)) Tj ET
q 0 G 1 w 50 600 m 382 600 l S Q
q 0.85 g 50 575 332 18 re f Q
BT 0 g /F2 11 Tf 55 580 Td (Scenario: Hitting) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 9 Tf 50 558 Td (What they're feeling: Angry, frustrated, overwhelmed) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F2 9 Tf 50 542 Td (What to SAY:) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F1 9 Tf 60 529 Td ("I won't let you hit. You're mad! You can stomp your feet or hit this pillow.") Tj ET
BT 0 g /F2 9 Tf 50 513 Td (What NOT to say:) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F1 9 Tf 60 500 Td ("Stop hitting! What's wrong with you? Bad boy/girl!") Tj ET
BT 0 g /F2 9 Tf 50 484 Td (What to DO:) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F1 9 Tf 60 471 Td (Block the hit gently. Stay calm. Offer an alternative physical outlet.) Tj ET
q 0.85 g 50 436 332 18 re f Q
BT 0 g /F2 11 Tf 55 441 Td (Scenario: Biting) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 9 Tf 50 419 Td (What they're feeling: Frustrated, overstimulated, teething pain, exploring) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F2 9 Tf 50 403 Td (What to SAY:) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F1 9 Tf 60 390 Td ("Ouch, biting hurts! You're frustrated. Let's find something safe to bite.") Tj ET
BT 0 g /F2 9 Tf 50 374 Td (What NOT to say:) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F1 9 Tf 60 361 Td ("Bite them back so they know how it feels!") Tj ET
BT 0 g /F2 9 Tf 50 345 Td (What to DO:) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F1 9 Tf 60 332 Td (Offer a teething toy. Remove from situation briefly. Stay neutral.) Tj ET

endstream
endobj
