BT 0 g /F2 13 Tf 97.44 610 Td (Emotion Coaching Scripts \(Page 2 of 5\)) Tj ET
q 0 G 1 w 50 600 m 382 600 l S Q
q 0.85 g 50 575 332 18 re f Q
BT 0 g /F2 11 Tf 55 580 Td (Scenario: Not Sharing) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 9 Tf 50 558 Td (What they're feeling: Possessive \(developmentally normal\), anxious about losing things) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F2 9 Tf 50 542 Td (What to SAY:) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F1 9 Tf 60 529 Td ("You're not ready to share that yet. That's okay. When you're done, it will be Maya's turn.") Tj ET
BT 0 g /F2 9 Tf 50 513 Td (What NOT to say:) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F1 9 Tf 60 500 Td ("Share right now or I'm taking it away!") Tj ET
BT 0 g /F2 9 Tf 50 484 Td (What to DO:) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F1 9 Tf 60 471 Td (Teach turn-taking, not forced sharing. Use a timer for turns.) Tj ET
q 0.85 g 50 436 332 18 re f Q
BT 0 g /F2 11 Tf 55 441 Td (Scenario: Bedtime Resistance) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 9 Tf 50 419 Td (What they're feeling: Fear of separation, not tired, need for control) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F2 9 Tf 50 403 Td (What to SAY:) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F1 9 Tf 60 390 Td ("I know you don't want bedtime. It's hard to stop playing. Would you like one more story or one more song?") Tj ET
BT 0 g /F2 9 Tf 50 374 Td (What NOT to say:) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F1 9 Tf 60 361 Td ("Get in bed NOW or no dessert tomorrow!") Tj ET
BT 0 g /F2 9 Tf 50 345 Td (What to DO:) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F1 9 Tf 60 332 Td (Offer limited choices. Keep routine consistent. Stay boring but present.) Tj ET

endstream
endobj
