BT 0 g /F2 13 Tf 97.44 610 Td (Emotion Coaching Scripts \(Page 4 of 5\)) Tj ET
q 0 G 1 w 50 600 m 382 600 l S Q
q 0.85 g 50 575 332 18 re f Q
BT 0 g /F2 11 Tf 55 580 Td (Scenario: Sibling Conflict) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 9 Tf 50 558 Td (What they're feeling: Jealousy, need for attention, boundary testing) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F2 9 Tf 50 542 Td (What to SAY:) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F1 9 Tf 60 529 Td ("You both want the truck. That's hard! Let's figure this out together.") Tj ET
BT 0 g /F2 9 Tf 50 513 Td (What NOT to say:) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F1 9 Tf 60 500 Td ("Why can't you just get along? Be nice to your sister!") Tj ET
BT 0 g /F2 9 Tf 50 484 Td (What to DO:) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F1 9 Tf 60 471 Td (Sportscaster the conflict. Don't take sides. Coach problem-solving.) Tj ET
q 0.85 g 50 436 332 18 re f Q
BT 0 g /F2 11 Tf 55 441 Td (Scenario: Public Meltdowns) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 9 Tf 50 419 Td (What they're feeling: Overstimulated, hungry, tired, embarrassed) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F2 9 Tf 50 403 Td (What to SAY:) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F1 9 Tf 60 390 Td ("This is too much right now. Let's find a quiet spot together.") Tj ET
BT 0 g /F2 9 Tf 50 374 Td (What NOT to say:) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F1 9 Tf 60 361 Td ("Everyone is looking at us. Stop it right now!") Tj ET
BT 0 g /F2 9 Tf 50 345 Td (What to DO:) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F1 9 Tf 60 332 Td (Leave if possible. Ignore stares. Your child's needs > strangers' opinions.) Tj ET

endstream
endobj
